<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">[[ Pseudogramma australis ]]</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
Randall &amp; Baldwin (1997) revised the fishes of the subtribe Pseudogrammina (Serranidae: Epinephelinae: Grammistini) and described five new Indo-Pacific species in the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:330B8E57-01EE-47A0-BAF1-0ED5C6E011E9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma Bleeker 1875:2, 24" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudogramma</taxonomicName>
. The description of one of these, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
, was based on specimens from Easter Island (first recorded as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:330B8E57-01EE-47A0-BAF1-0ED5C6E011E9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma Bleeker 1875:2, 24" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudogramma sp.</taxonomicName>
by Randall &amp; Cea 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Egaña">Egana</normalizedToken>
, 1984), Pitcairn Island, Gambier Group of the Tuamotu Archipelago, Rarotonga in the Cook Islands, and Ofolanga Island of the Ha’apai Group in Tonga.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">Randall &amp; Baldwin noted that the Easter Island specimens were red in life while the only western specimens for which there was information on color, the Tuamotu and Tonga fish, were yellow. However, all had basically the same pattern of rows of whitish blotches, irregular rows of dark red dots on the head, scattered dark red dots on the body, and a paleedged dark blotch on the opercle. The Easter Island specimens have modally one more dorsal ray and pectoral ray, two more anal rays, and 10 + 17 instead of 10+16 vertebrae. Easter Island is the most southern of the localities, so Randall and Baldwin wrote that it is possible that the meristic differences may be due to the lower sea temperature at Easter. They added, however, that they believed the differences were more likely genetic and elected to treat the Easter Island population as subspecifically different from the Pitcairn to Tonga populations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
We have re-examined the specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Pseudogramma australis</taxonomicName>
, including five more uncatalogued specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
from the Bishop Museum collected at Easter Island since 1997, and we conclude that the western populations are deserving of specific status. Not mentioned previously is the larger size of Easter Island fish. The 14 Easter Island specimens collected from six stations vary from 35-61 mm SL, with only the 35 mm specimen less than 40 mm. The 12 specimens from seven stations from Pitcairn to Tonga measure 22.4-41.0 mm SL, with only two specimens, 39.1 and 41.0 mm, larger than 35 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Table 5 of the description of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Pseudogramma australis</taxonomicName>
(Randall &amp; Baldwin, 1997: 21), showing the proportional measurements of eight type specimens, includes one of 26.0 mm SL from Rarotonga and one of 33.1 mm SL from Pitcairn Island. These are the two smallest specimens measured; all the others in the table are from Easter Island. These two specimens have a larger head, longer snout, larger eye, longer upper jaw, and longer predorsal length than the Easter Island specimens. It was originally assumed that these differences were ontogenetic. Now that we have measured the remaining specimens from western localities, it is apparent that these differences are diagnostic of two different species. Herein we recognize 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
as comprising two species, one from Easter Island and the other from the western Pacific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="BPBM" country="Chile" location="Easter Island" specimenCode="BPBM 6623" stateProvince="Easter Island" typeStatus="holotype">
A specimen from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:95335B85CDDCAFBEA6264CCEEA489D90:D607BB8B101CC0FFA9C1836A15A99F37" name="Easter Island">Easter Island</location>
, 52.9 mm SL (
<specimenCode>
<collectionCode>BPBM</collectionCode>
6623
</specimenCode>
), was designated as the 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Pseudogramma australis</taxonomicName>
.
</materialsCitation>
Instead of naming the Easter Island subspecies 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
, Randall &amp; Baldwin named it 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">P. a. pasquensis</taxonomicName>
(from the Spanish name for Easter Island, Isla de Pascua), and designated the same Easter Island specimen (BPBM 6623) as the holotype of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">P. a. pasquensis</taxonomicName>
. Simultaneously, they designated a holotype from Temoe Atoll (BPBM 13531) for the western subspecies they named 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
. These type designations in the original descriptions of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">P. a. pasquensis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
(Randall &amp; Baldwin, 1997:23) have created nomenclatural conflicts that we resolve herein using the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (1999; abbreviated hereafter as ICZN).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Two of the names, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">P. a. pasquensis</taxonomicName>
, are based on the same name-bearing type specimen (BPBM 6623). When synonyms are established simultaneously, Article 24.1 of the ICZN requires the name proposed at the higher rank to take precedence. In this case, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">australis</taxonomicName>
was proposed for a species and must take precedence over 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">pasquensis</taxonomicName>
, which was proposed as a subspecies. Thus, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607DD51E-1EC1-43F1-916A-710C5E4F9F74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis pasquensis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:23" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="pasquensis">P. a. pasquensis</taxonomicName>
is considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Two of the names, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
and its nominotypical taxon 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
, are based on different name-bearing types (BPBM 6623 for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
, BPBM 13531 for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
). Article 61.2.1 of the ICZN indicates: “If different name-bearing types are fixed simultaneously for a nominal taxon and for its nominotypical taxon, the fixation for the taxon at higher rank takes precedence.” The holotype of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
is therefore fixed as BPBM 6623 from Easter Island, and the name 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25C9FDEA-1274-4B90-B156-12E35AD47609" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma australis Randall &amp; Baldwin 1997:19" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">P. australis</taxonomicName>
does not apply to the western Pacific species. The name 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8F695BC2-8B78-454F-93A4-09DC18C542FC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma xanthum Randall, Baldwin &amp; Williams 2002:3" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthum">P. xanthum</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel>nomen novum</taxonomicNameLabel>
is provided herein as a new replacement name for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="australis" subSpecies="australis">P. a. australis</taxonomicName>
. As required by ICZN Article 72.7, the holotype (BPBM 13531) for the replacement name, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8F695BC2-8B78-454F-93A4-09DC18C542FC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma xanthum Randall, Baldwin &amp; Williams 2002:3" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthum">P. xanthum</taxonomicName>
, is the same as that of the name it replaces. Based on our examination of all available specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8F695BC2-8B78-454F-93A4-09DC18C542FC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Pseudogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudogramma xanthum Randall, Baldwin &amp; Williams 2002:3" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthum">P. xanthum</taxonomicName>
, the species is redescribed.
</paragraph>
